There will be two classes,

Player

and

Game

The player class will contain the players scores, the players lives, and the player's name. Requires a name to intialize.

The Game class will contain which turn it is, a method to determine if either player's score has reached 0 and output game over, a random number method that picks two numbers to add together, a method to determine if the answer is correct or not and update the relevant players score. This class will handle player input and output.
Requires the instances of the players to be intialized.